        <TextBlock FontSize="20" FontFamily="Garamond" Margin="100,284,817.333,97.667" TextWrapping="Wrap"><Run Text="•  2 x 400g cans cherry tomatoes "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  400g can mixed bean salad, drained "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  200g baby spinach "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  4 medium eggs "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  50g thinly sliced smoked ham, torn "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  wholemeal rye bread, to serve (optional)"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="  "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="STEP 1 "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Tip the tomatoes and bean salad into an ovenproof frying pan or shallow flameproof casserole dish. Simmer for 10 mins, or until reduced. Stir in the spinach and cook for 5 mins more until wilted.  "/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="STEP 2 "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="Heat the grill to medium. Make four indentations in the mixture using the back of a spoon, then crack one egg in each. Nestle the ham in the mixture, then grill for 4-5 mins, or until the whites are set and the yolks runny. Serve with rye bread, if you like."/></TextBlock>
        <Button x:Name="SaveRecipe1" Background="#FF22223B" Width="173" Height="36" Margin="299,701,1033.333,215.667" Content="Save Recipe" Foreground="White" FontFamily="Garamond" FontSize="25" Click="SaveRecipe1_Click"></Button>
        <Image Margin="508,267,817.333,510.667" Width="180" Height="175
               ">
